♪ Of your ornament tree

1041
01:34:51,522 --> 01:34:56,234
♪ For it stood on your shore

1042
01:34:57,319 --> 01:35:00,988
♪ For many's the long day

1043
01:35:01,115 --> 01:35:07,662
♪ 'Til the long boats from Antrim

1044
01:35:07,788 --> 01:35:14,127
♪ Came to float it away

1045
01:35:15,671 --> 01:35:20,508
♪ Oh Bonny Portmore

1046
01:35:20,634 --> 01:35:25,388
♪ You shine where you stand

1047
01:35:25,514 --> 01:35:30,727
♪ And the more I think on you

1048
01:35:30,853 --> 01:35:35,106
♪ The more I think long

1049
01:35:35,232 --> 01:35:39,485
♪ If I had you now

1050
01:35:39,611 --> 01:35:44,699
♪ As I had once before

1051
01:35:44,825 --> 01:35:51,205
♪ All the Lords in Old England

1052
01:35:51,331 --> 01:35:58,171
♪ Would not purchase Portmore

1053
01:35:59,548 --> 01:36:04,719
♪ All the birds in the forest

1054
01:36:04,845 --> 01:36:08,890
♪ They bitterly weep

1055
01:36:09,016 --> 01:36:14,312
♪ Saying, "Where shall we shelter?

1056
01:36:14,438 --> 01:36:18,858
♪ "Where shall we sleep?"

1057
01:36:18,984 --> 01:36:22,945
♪ For the oak and the ash

1058
01:36:23,071 --> 01:36:28,743
♪ They are all cutten down

1059
01:36:28,869 --> 01:36:35,249
♪ And the walls of Bonny Portmore

1060
01:36:35,375 --> 01:36:42,131
♪ Are all down to the ground

